sentences.explanationText: 【嘅ge3】: a structural particle indicating possession or attribution, equivalent to Mandarin “的” or English" ’s "or of.

sentences.english: Mr. Pig made breakfast and let her to eat it in bed.
sentences.explanationText:
【整zing2】= make ; 【verb+咗zo2】=action is completed →【zing2 zo2】=made
【早餐zou2 caan1】=breakfast;
【等佢dang2 keoi5】= let her/him
【床cong4】=bed
【度dou6】=place; spot; boundaries; sphere of an activity or a state

sentences.english: Pepper and George made a birthday card for Mrs. Pig.
sentences.explanationText:
【生日咭sang1 jat6 kat2】=birthday card
【畀bie2】=to give

sentences.english: Mummy Pig: "Oh! This is a surprise birthday present."
sentences.explanationText:
【驚喜 ging1 hei2】=surprise
【禮物 lai5 mat6】=gift; present

lessons.title: 17/12/2025 A Sunday with Ah Ming’s Family

sentences.english: Good morning, I am Ah Ming.
On Sunday, I went with my dad, mom, and elder sister to have dim sum with Grandpa and Grandma.
As we were leaving, mum looked at the sky and said,
sentences.explanationText:
果陣（jgwo2 zan6）=at that time
望(mong6)=look; 住(jyu6）：a Cantonese aspect particle indicating a continuous action；→望住（mong6 zyu6）=be looking at

sentences.english: Hmm, it's overcast, looks like it might rain,
sentences.explanationText:
天陰陰（tin1 jam1 jam1）=overcast；
好似（hou2 ci5）=seems like/looks like;
想（soeng2）=about to/going to；
落雨（lok6 jyu5）=to rain；
喎（wo3）：A Cantonese sentence-final particle used to add a tone of "reminding" or "informing the listener".

sentences.english: Grandpa had already arrived. We sat down,
sentences.explanationText:
早就（zou2 zau6）:already (done) a long time ago.
到（dou3）=arrive；咗（zo2）：perfective aspect particle.→到咗（dou3 zo2）=have already arrived.
坐低（zo6 dai1）=sit down

sentences.english: "Have you been winning or losing more at Chinese chess recently?"

sentences.explanationText:
笑（siu3）=smile、laugh; 住（zyu6）： a Cantonese continuous aspect particle.→笑住（siu3 zyu6）：while smiling (doing an action).
答（daap3）=replied

梗係（gang2 hai6）=of course、definitely；
啦（laa1）=A Cantonese sentence-final particle used to add a tone of "certainty" or "emphasis".

sentences.english: The family had some tea, chatted, and that's the happiest way to spend time.
sentences.explanationText:
一家人（jat1 gaa1 jan4）=the whole family;
飲茶（jam2  caa4）=have tea (often referring to dim sum tea time);下（haa6）:a particle indicating "casually, continuously doing".→飲下茶（jam2 haa6 caa4）=while having tea；
傾偈（king1 gai2）=chat, have a casual talk；
最（zeoi3）=most
開心（hoi1 sam1）=happy
就係（zau6 hai6）=it is；咁（gam2）=like this (state) → 就係咁（zau6 hai6 gam2）=it’s just like this
